What happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?
When you initialize a repostiroy, several meta-data files are created. You need to do to track
files in the repository directory.

How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository? What value do you think it offers?
The staing area connects the working directory to the repository. The staging area allows you to 
choose which files to commit instead of commiting all the files in the working directory at once.
